This paper deals with the security and communication aspects of mobile P2P networks, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also proposes a formal analysis of the proposed mechanism, which falls under the sub-category of formal methods (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the collaborative nature of the proposed mechanism, which can be studied in the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
